# Premium Artist Portfolio Website

Build a cinematic, Apple-style portfolio for Pankaj (Pencil & Charcoal Realism Artist) using Next.js 14, Tailwind CSS, and Framer Motion.

## Existing Assets

| Asset            | Path                                            | Details                          |
| ---------------- | ----------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| Profile pics     | `d:\portfolio\profile picture\`                 | 3 files (1 JPEG, 2 HEIC)         |
| Gallery artworks | `d:\portfolio\gallery data\img 1` – `img 18`    | 18 folders, each with 2-4 images |
| Reel videos      | `d:\portfolio\gallery data\reel video section\` | 12 MP4/MOV files                 |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> HEIC profile images will need conversion to JPEG/WebP for browser compatibility. The 3 large videos (390MB, 611MB, 235MB) are too large for Vercel; we'll use placeholder thumbnails and recommend hosting videos on YouTube/cloud storage for production.

## User Review Required

1. **Video hosting**: The reel videos total ~1.3GB. For production, they should be hosted on YouTube/Cloudflare Stream and embedded. For the dev build, we'll use small sample videos and a placeholder approach.
2. **HEIC images**: The 2 HEIC profile pictures need conversion. I'll use the JPEG one directly and generate placeholder crops for the carousel.
3. **About section intro video**: No intro video was found in assets. We'll add a placeholder with instructions for you to drop in your actual video.
4. **Social media links**: I'll use `#` placeholders — you can update them in the data file.

